  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The attack was either going to come through the south or through the north, so it was strategically important to keep those rail lines open because that's how the German army moved, rapidly with rail.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There was not enough time to move a division, and it would have consumed too much fuel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The mission of this Bat'ko squad was basically to interdict the Trencin-Gilena main line, which continued then in Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were under strict orders not to engage in any kind of action with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The objective was to hit, strike, and disappear as quickly as possible.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We had more than enough ammunition.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had more enough explosives.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The problem was carrying the explosives, and they were very glad to use me as a carrier when I was not walking ahead of the squad as a way of leading them in the right direction.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The objective was to find a part of the track where the track was on a curve and blow up one of the rails so that the weight, the heavy weight of the front end of the train-- which was usually in the tender, where the water was and the coal was stored-- would tilt the, the, the machine off the track and fall off an embankment, and thereby block the, the rail line.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Clearly, we could not stop the traffic, but we surely could make it difficult and uncertain to have predicted troop movements over those lines because a loss of half a day or even a day in a key offensive when you are moving troops becomes a very critical element.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it would generally take a day or a half, something like a day--",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
